    "body": "If a user simply upgrades without changing any configuration and Erigon no longer works, I consider that a breaking change. Release notes should include warnings and instructions to avoid breaking changes.\r\n\r\n[v2.43.0](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/releases/tag/v2.43.0) was a breaking change because anyone who had the `--externalcl` flag set found that Erigon would not startup and the error message did not explain why. It only said `flag provided but not defined: -externalcl` and immediately failed startup.\r\n\r\nSeveral people in the discord (besides me) had this same issue and thus friction and delay was added to their upgrade.\r\n\r\nThis could be avoided with a simple message in the release notes:\r\n`Breaking change: If you have --externalcl in your configuration, _remove it_ before restarting Erigon. External CL usage is now the default`\r\n\r\nInstead I see: `Added first phase of Caplin (embeddable Consensus Layer implementation), replaces embedded CL light client. Disabled by default, enabled by --internalcl command line flag.` which might raise alarm bells with the most savvy operators but it's not a clear call to action.\r\n\r\n",
